array.name: faq_functions_examples
array.item: asin(x) - the arc sine of x \nThe result is in the range -pi/2…pi/2(or -90...90, depends on the mode) \nExample: \'asin(0.5)\'
acos(x) - the arc cosine of x \nThe result is in the range 0...pi(or 0...180, depends on the mode) \nExample: \'acos(0.5)\'
atan(x) - the arc tangent of x \nthe result is in the range -pi/2...pi/2(or -90...90, depends on the mode) \nExample: \'atan(33)\'
acot(x) - the arc cotangent of x \nthe result is in the range 0...pi(or 0...180, depends on the mode) \nExample: \'acot(33)\'
sinh(x) - the hyperbolic sine of x \nExample: \'sinh(25)\'
cosh(x) - the hyperbolic cosine of x \nExample: \'cosh(25)\'
tanh(x) - the hyperbolic tangent of x \nExample: \'tanh(32)\'
coth(x) - the hyperbolic cotangent of x \nExample: \'coth(32)\'
